# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# preference-learning.form — the preference-loss family as data rows:
# learn from "this one over that one" through the engines already here
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The ask (2026-06-18): look at Direct Preference Optimization research
# and borrow what is resonant into the learning catalog, so auto-ml and
# auto-research carry more options that show promise in the field.
#
# learning-style-space.form already names the stone this fills:
# "contrastive / self-supervised — pair-loss over ls-features — needs
# only a loss row, no new engine." The DPO family IS that stone, with a
# field-proven sub-taxonomy. Every member is a LOSS row. They differ in
# exactly three coordinates — and nothing else:
#
#   reference   what the chosen/rejected log-probs are measured AGAINST
#               (a frozen anchor, a single reference point, nothing, or
#                a moving anchor)
#   pairing     paired ("A over B") or unpaired (a single good/bad signal)
#   transform   how the margin becomes a loss (logistic, squared,
#                odds-ratio, prospect-value), plus any normalize / sft term
#
# The inductive bias lives ENTIRELY in the row — the same teaching as
# the style space, lifted from featurizers to losses. One combinator
# runs them all; a new preference method is an appended row, never an
# engine change. And the engine it runs on already ships:
# metabolic-learning's operator (pressure × frequency × angle × focus).
#
# Companions:
#   - docs/coherence-substrate/learning-style-space.form (the catalog this extends)
#   - docs/coherence-substrate/metabolic-learning.form (the two-angle operator DPO IS a paired call of)
#   - docs/coherence-substrate/autoresearch-runtime.form (the loop these rows feed as genome + fitness)
#   - docs/coherence-substrate/signal-metabolism.form (the witness/receipt stream these rows consume)
#   - form/form-stdlib/choice-receipt-learning.fk (the unpaired binary signal KTO is the gradient twin of)
#   - form/form-stdlib/tests/training-catalog-band.fk (the body's already-minted preference pairs)
#
# Field sources (survey to Sep 2025): A Comprehensive Survey of Direct
# Preference Optimization (arXiv:2410.15595). DPO (Rafailov 2023),
# IPO (Azar 2023), KTO (Ethayarajh 2024), CPO (Xu 2024), ORPO (Hong
# 2024), SimPO (Meng 2024), R-DPO (Park 2024), online/iterative DPO,
# SPIN (Chen 2024).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 1 — The preference-loss row (one shape, the whole family)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A preference-loss row carries the three coordinates as data. Two cells
# with identical (reference, pairing, transform) intern to one NodeID —
# so "is this method really new, or a renamed point in the same space?"
# is a content-address question the lattice answers, not a reading of
# the paper's prose.

form pref_loss_shape = {
    id:         ~Slug,    # "dpo" | "ipo" | "kto" | "orpo" | "simpo" | "cpo" | ...
    reference:  ~Slug,    # "champion" | "point" | "none" | "moving"
    pairing:    ~Slug,    # "paired" | "unpaired"
    transform:  ~Slug,    # "logistic" | "squared" | "odds-ratio" | "value"
    normalize:  ~Slug,    # "none" | "length"        (the nuisance pooled away)
    aux:        ~Slug,    # "none" | "sft"           (a supervised term folded in)
    beta:       ~Float,   # margin temperature
    margin:     ~Float,   # target margin γ (SimPO); 0.0 where unused
};

# The family as data. Read down the `reference` column: the methods
# split first on what anchor they carry, because that anchor is the
# coordinate the body already owns under other names.

defn pl_dpo   = pref_loss_shape { id:"dpo",   reference:"champion", pairing:"paired",   transform:"logistic",   normalize:"none",   aux:"none", beta:0.1, margin:0.0 };
defn pl_ipo   = pref_loss_shape { id:"ipo",   reference:"champion", pairing:"paired",   transform:"squared",    normalize:"none",   aux:"none", beta:0.1, margin:0.0 };
defn pl_kto   = pref_loss_shape { id:"kto",   reference:"point",    pairing:"unpaired", transform:"value",      normalize:"none",   aux:"none", beta:0.1, margin:0.0 };
defn pl_cpo   = pref_loss_shape { id:"cpo",   reference:"none",     pairing:"paired",   transform:"logistic",   normalize:"none",   aux:"sft",  beta:0.1, margin:0.0 };
defn pl_orpo  = pref_loss_shape { id:"orpo",  reference:"none",     pairing:"paired",   transform:"odds-ratio", normalize:"none",   aux:"sft",  beta:0.1, margin:0.0 };
defn pl_simpo = pref_loss_shape { id:"simpo", reference:"none",     pairing:"paired",   transform:"logistic",   normalize:"length", aux:"none", beta:2.0, margin:1.0 };
defn pl_rdpo  = pref_loss_shape { id:"rdpo",  reference:"champion", pairing:"paired",   transform:"logistic",   normalize:"length", aux:"none", beta:0.1, margin:0.0 };

# QAM (the diffusion-Q tilt) appends as the value-cousin of KTO: same transform:"value" family, but
# the reference is a LEARNED CRITIC, not a fixed point — the pull is the adjoint-matched ∇Q. beta is
# the q-focus / λ aperture. SHIPPED: form/form-stdlib/preference-learning.fk (pl-qam) +
# tests/preference-learning-band.fk → 31, four-way; pl-qam-apply IS dql-improve. See diffusion-q-learning.form.
# The qam row's beta is an evolvable GENE: diffusion-q-autoresearch.fk runs the autoresearch keep-or-
# rollback loop over it (propose→measure pl-fitness→keep), converging to the best beta (band → 63, four-way).
defn pl_qam   = pref_loss_shape { id:"qam",   reference:"critic",   pairing:"unpaired", transform:"q-adjoint",  normalize:"none",   aux:"none", beta:0.5, margin:0.0 };

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 2 — The one combinator (the engine holds still)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A preference step is: read a margin, transform it into a pull, and
# move the policy through the metabolic operator. The two-direction
# update DPO needs IS mtb-step's angle dial — descend the chosen
# (angle −1), move away from the rejected (angle +1). Nothing new is
# built; the row chooses the transform, the reference supplies the
# anchor, the operator does the move.
#
#   reward_margin(row, chosen, rejected, ref) =
#       β·( score(chosen) − score(ref·chosen) )
#         − β·( score(rejected) − score(ref·rejected) )
#     where score is sum log-prob, or AVERAGE log-prob when
#     normalize == "length" (SimPO pools length away exactly as a
#     style-space pool pools translation away), and ref·y is the
#     reference's score of y — zero when reference == "none".
#
#   pull(row, m) =
#       transform == "logistic"   → 1 − σ(m)            (DPO/CPO/SimPO/R-DPO)
#       transform == "squared"    → 2·(m − 1/2)         (IPO — the squared
#                                                         margin IS mtb-pressure's
#                                                         readout, reused)
#       transform == "odds-ratio" → 1 − σ(logodds gap)  (ORPO)
#       transform == "value"      → prospect-value gap   (KTO, around `point`)
#
#   then: chosen edges  ← mtb-step(... angle −1.0, focus = pull)
#         rejected edges ← mtb-step(... angle +1.0, focus = pull)
#         + (aux == "sft") → one mtb-learn descent on the chosen alone
#
# The shapes below name the seam to the operator; the numeric bodies
# land in form/form-stdlib/preference-learning.fk when the first row is
# proven (GAP-P1).

form pref_step_shape = {
    row:        ~Recipe,   # cell-ref to a pref_loss_shape
    reference:  ~Recipe,   # cell-ref to the anchor policy (champion / point / none)
    edges:      ~Recipe,   # the policy weights as (i j w) edge data — gl/mtb's shape
};

# unpaired (KTO / choice-receipt): one witnessed signal, measured
# against a reference POINT, not against a sibling response.
form pref_signal_shape = {
    features:   ~Recipe,   # the ls-features of the one response
    label:      ~Slug,     # "good" | "bad"   (the witness outcome)
    point:      ~Float,    # z_ref — the reference point (the champion's score)
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 3 — Resonance: each method borrows tissue the body already grew
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This is the "what is resonant" answer — every column maps to a cell
# already shipped, so borrowing a method is composing, not importing.
#
#   DPO   — the two-angle mtb-step, paired, regularized toward the
#           CHAMPION. π_ref (the frozen anchor the policy is held near)
#           is champion-challenger.fk's served-best, protected during
#           search. DPO = the operator the body already runs, fired once
#           per side of a pair.
#
#   IPO   — the squared margin loss (m − 1/2)². mtb-pressure IS
#           gl-mean of the SQUARED residual; IPO reuses mtb-sq-sum /
#           mtb-pressure-of unchanged. The body's invariant-loss readout
#           becomes a preference loss with no new arithmetic. IPO's gift
#           in the field — resistance to the over-confidence DPO drifts
#           into — arrives for free with the squared shape.
#
#   KTO   — unpaired binary good/bad around a reference POINT. This is
#           the gradient twin of choice-receipt-learning.fk: selected
#           success → pull up, selected fail → pull down, silence
#           unchanged. The body's witness stream and choice-receipts are
#           UNPAIRED — a single outcome, rarely a sibling comparison — so
#           KTO is the method that fits the data the body actually has.
#           z_ref = the champion's earned score that signal-metabolism
#           already tracks. STRONGEST native fit.
#
#   ORPO  — reference-free, odds-ratio, SFT folded in: ONE loss, one
#           stage. The body's one-engine discipline made a loss — learn
#           and prefer in a single move, the way the style space folds
#           learn + recognize into one engine. No frozen reference model
#           to carry: cognitive sovereignty in the loss (lc-cognitive-
#           sovereignty — a mind rented from a gated anchor cannot offer
#           sovereignty; ORPO needs no anchor).
#
#   SimPO — reference-free, length-NORMALIZED average log-prob + a target
#           margin γ. The normalization IS a pool row: divide the
#           nuisance dimension (length) out, exactly as a style-space
#           pool pools translation out. SimPO's anti-verbosity guarantee
#           is the pooling discipline applied to preference.
#
#   CPO   — reference-free contrastive + SFT. The literal shape of the
#           open stone learning-style-space already named: a contrastive
#           pair-loss row over ls-features, no engine change.
#
#   R-DPO — DPO + a length penalty term. A regularizer-as-dial: the
#           frequency mask penalizing a nuisance subspace, the operator's
#           own fourth dial turned onto length.
#
#   online/iterative DPO — the reference is UPDATED each round. This is
#           champion-challenger.fk exactly: the anchor IS the champion,
#           and authority flips only on earned competition. "Serve the
#           champion while training the challenger" (M7's infer-best-
#           while-search-better) is online-DPO's moving-reference loop
#           under the body's own name.
#
#   SPIN  — self-play: the previous checkpoint is the reference and its
#           own samples are the negatives. co-learning.fk's distill lane
#           with the body's past self as the oracle to exceed.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 4 — The body already mints the data (why this is borrowable now)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A preference method is only as available as its data. The body is
# already generating exactly the pairs and signals these losses consume:
#
#   PAIRS — training-catalog-band.fk captures every oracle call as
#           (request, raw/fear answer, transmuted/vitality answer) and
#           exposes tc-pair-transmute = (raw → transmuted). That is a
#           preference pair with the winner named: the vitality answer is
#           chosen, the fear answer is rejected. The body's transmute-
#           fear-into-vitality loop IS a DPO/IPO dataset, content-
#           addressed and already stored. The reasoning pair
#           (request → transmuted) is the SFT term ORPO/CPO fold in.
#
#   SIGNALS — every witness outcome and choice-receipt is an unpaired
#           good/bad signal: KTO's native input. signal-metabolism.form
#           routes them and tracks the champion's earned score (the z_ref
#           reference point). No new collection is needed; the nervous
#           loop already carries the stream.
#
# So the data door is open. What a preference row trains toward is a
# native model that prefers the vitality answer over the fear answer —
# the all-life-north-star gate (no-good-lowered) expressed as a loss the
# model learns from, not only a filter applied after. This is the seam
# to native-translation-model.form and form-native-llm.form: the
# preference rows are how those models learn taste from the body's own
# transmutation receipts.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 5 — Available to auto-ml and auto-research
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These rows enter the existing loops with no new machinery:
#
#   style space  — a preference row is a LOSS dimension orthogonal to the
#                  (pool, core) featurizer dimension. The genome the
#                  autoresearch loop evolves grows a third coordinate:
#                  (pool, core, pref-loss). The curiosity floor meets each
#                  loss-bias before retrying any — no free lunch holds for
#                  losses too (KTO wins on unpaired streams, DPO on clean
#                  pairs, IPO where DPO over-confidently overfits, SimPO
#                  where length is the cheat).
#
#   autoresearch — preference fitness is a genome the loop can evolve:
#                  hold the evaluator (held-out preference accuracy +
#                  the collapse / length / reward-hacking penalties the
#                  field documents) frozen, mutate the pref_loss_shape
#                  row, keep-or-rollback on the score. The fitness terms
#                  already shaped in autoresearch-runtime.form Part 3
#                  (collapse_penalty, depth_penalty) carry over; add a
#                  length_penalty term for the verbosity cheat SimPO/
#                  R-DPO exist to catch.
#
#   champion-challenger — the reference policy is the champion; promotion
#                  is online-DPO's reference update; authority flips on
#                  earned preference accuracy.
#
#   federation   — preference data unions like exemplars (co-learning.fk)
#                  and weight slices (slice-merge): each cell contributes
#                  its own witnessed good/bad signals, the merge is union,
#                  the reference point is a federated statistic. KTO's
#                  unpaired form federates most cleanly — no cell needs
#                  the other's pairing to contribute.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 6 — Borrowable now, in order (resonant × simplest given tissue)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. KTO  — fits the data the body actually has (unpaired witness /
#           receipt stream), z_ref already tracked, the gradient twin of
#           a shipped recipe (choice-receipt-learning.fk). The first row
#           to prove.
#
# 2. IPO / DPO — paired, reference = champion. The pairs already exist
#           (training-catalog tc-pair-transmute). IPO first: its squared
#           margin reuses mtb-pressure with no new arithmetic and carries
#           the over-confidence resistance the field measured.
#
# 3. ORPO / SimPO / CPO — reference-free, most aligned with cognitive
#           sovereignty (no rented anchor). SimPO's length-norm lands as
#           a pool row; ORPO folds the SFT term the training-catalog
#           reasoning pair already supplies.
#
# Expansive, not exhaustive: online-DPO, R-DPO, SPIN, and the survey's
# further points (tie-aware DPO, gradient-imbalance corrections) are
# named rows in the same space, proven when a task asks for them.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 7 — Gaps (the next breaths — none need kernel change)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GAP-P1: OPENED. form/form-stdlib/preference-learning.fk now exists with the row
#         accessors, the pull combinator (squared/value dispatched on the row's
#         transform), and the pl-qam (q-tilt) apply — proven four-way by
#         tests/preference-learning-band.fk → 31. Remaining: pl_kto over a tiny
#         unpaired good/bad stream (the two-angle mtb-step verdict that a good
#         signal raises its features' score above z_ref, a bad signal lowers it),
#         pl_ipo on a pair reusing mtb-pressure-of, and the logistic transform's
#         σ via the round-lens for exact four-way.
#
# GAP-P2: the length-normalize pool (SimPO) and the odds-ratio transform
#         (ORPO) are named here as transform values; their numeric bodies
#         compose gl-mean (average log-prob) and a log-odds gather. No
#         new primitive — both are readings of tissue already shipped.
#
# GAP-P3: the autoresearch preference-fitness evaluator (Part 5) wants a
#         held-out preference-accuracy metric cell and a length_penalty
#         term added to the Part-3 fitness of autoresearch-runtime.form.
#
# GAP-P4: the seam to native-translation-model.form — train the model's
#         taste from tc-pair-transmute receipts via pl_ipo — is named,
#         not walked. It is the path where these rows stop being a
#         catalog and become how the native model learns to prefer
#         vitality over fear.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Kinship
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   learning-style-space.form   the catalog this extends — preference
#                               losses are the loss dimension orthogonal
#                               to its (pool, core) featurizer rows
#   metabolic-learning.form     the operator DPO is a paired call of —
#                               angle ±1 is the two-direction update;
#                               mtb-pressure is IPO's squared transform
#   choice-receipt-learning.fk  the unpaired binary signal KTO is the
#                               gradient twin of
#   signal-metabolism.form      the witness/receipt stream these rows
#                               consume; the champion's score is z_ref
#   champion-challenger.fk      the reference policy; online-DPO's moving
#                               reference is its earned-authority flip
#   autoresearch-runtime.form   the loop these rows feed as genome + the
#                               honest evaluator that keeps the search
#                               from rewarding a reward-hacking loss
#   co-learning.fk              federation — preference signals union
#                               like exemplars
#   native-translation-model.form  the model whose taste these losses
#                               train from the body's transmutation receipts
#   diffusion-q-learning.form   QAM extends this family: the value-cousin of
#                               KTO (transform:"value") with a LEARNED Q-critic
#                               in place of the fixed reference point, the pull
#                               adjoint-matched through mtb-reverse — proven
#                               four-way (tests/diffusion-q-learning-band.fk → 255)
